2026-04-20 | Maximum Distance Between Houses with Different Colors

Question
Return maximum possible distance.
	Approach
1.	Observation:
		max distance will involve either:
			first house OR last house  
2.	Check from left:
		find farthest index j where colors[j] != colors[0]  
3.	Check from right:
		find farthest index i where colors[i] != colors[n-1]  
4.	Take maximum of both distances  
	Time Complexity
	O(n)
	Space Complexity
	O(1)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    int maxDistance(vector<int>& colors) {
        int n = colors.size();
        int ans = 0;
        // compare with first element
        for(int i = n - 1; i >= 0; i--){
            if(colors[i] != colors[0]){
                ans = max(ans, i);
                break;
            }
        }
        // compare with last element
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++){
            if(colors[i] != colors[n-1]){
                ans = max(ans, n - 1 - i);
                break;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
	Key Insight
The maximum distance must involve:
		an endpoint (0 or n-1)  
So we only check:
- farthest from first  
- farthest from last  
This avoids O(n²) brute force.
